 JOHANNESBURG - City Power says it wants to restore power to the Lotus substation by Monday. A fire at the site has left many residents in Johannesburg south without electricity. New cables have been delivered to the site, and technicians are testing them. City Power suspects the fire may have been caused by lightning but is investigating to determine if there was any foul play. #LotusOutage
City Power is attending to an outage at Lotus Substation.
Affected areas:
Zakariya Park
Vlakfontein
Hospital Hills
